      • getRegexName

        public static String getRegexName(StructuralNode sn,
                                  boolean incParams)
        Returns a regex pattern that will match the specified StructuralNode, ignoring the parent and children. For most nodes this will just be the last element in the path, eg URL regex name https://www.example.com/aaa/bbb bbb https://www.example.com/aaa aaa https://www.example.com/ https://www.example.com Datadriven nodes are different, they will always return (.+?) to match anything.
        Parameters:
        sn - a StructuralNode
        incParams - if true then include URL params in the regex, otherwise exclude them
        Returns:
        a regex pattern that will match the specified StructuralNode, ignoring the parent and children.

      • getCleanRelativeName

        public static String getCleanRelativeName(StructuralNode sn,
                                          boolean incParams)
        Returns the name of the node ignoring the parent and children, ie the last element in the path. Data driven nodes will return the user specified name surrounded by the double angled brackets.
        Parameters:
        sn - a StructuralNode
        incParams - if true then include URL params in the regex, otherwise exclude them
        Returns:
        the name of the node ignoring the parent and children
